======================================================================
PART 3: Difference operator and Stirling numbers
======================================================================

  I(x) = 1 + a1*x + a2*x^2
  Newton forward differences at 0:
    D^0 I(0) = 1
    D^1 I(0) = a1+a2
    D^2 I(0) = 2a2
    D^k I(0) = 0 for k>=3

  Newton: I(x) = C(x,0) + (a1+a2)*C(x,1) + 2a2*C(x,2)
  At x=2: I(2) = 1 + 2*(a1+a2) + 2a2 = 1 + 2a1 + 4a2
  At x=-1: I(-1) = 1 - (a1+a2) + 2a2 = 1 - a1 + a2

  Verification:
    a1=36, a2= 6: D=[1,42,12], H=97=97, I(-1)=-29=-29
    a1=37, a2= 4: D=[1,41,8], H=91=91, I(-1)=-32=-32
    a1=45, a2= 6: D=[1,51,12], H=115=115, I(-1)=-38=-38
    a1=28, a2= 4: D=[1,32,8], H=73=73, I(-1)=-23=-23
    a1=32, a2= 4: D=[1,36,8], H=81=81, I(-1)=-27=-27

======================================================================
PART 4: Cube root evaluation -- Eisenstein integers
======================================================================

  w = e^(2pi*i/3), w^2 + w + 1 = 0
  I(w) = 1 + a1*w + a2*w^2
  In Z[w]: I(w) = (1-a2) + (a1-a2)*w  [since w^2 = -1-w]

  Eisenstein norm N(I(w)) = (1-a2)^2 - (1-a2)(a1-a2) + (a1-a2)^2:
    a1=36, a2= 6: I(w)=(-5)+(30)w, N=1075, |I(w)|^2=1075.0, match=True
    a1=37, a2= 4: I(w)=(-3)+(33)w, N=1197, |I(w)|^2=1197.0, match=True
    a1=45, a2= 6: I(w)=(-5)+(39)w, N=1741, |I(w)|^2=1741.0, match=True
    a1=28, a2= 4: I(w)=(-3)+(24)w, N=657, |I(w)|^2=657.0, match=True
    a1=32, a2= 4: I(w)=(-3)+(28)w, N=877, |I(w)|^2=877.0, match=True
    a1=25, a2= 5: I(w)=(-4)+(20)w, N=496, |I(w)|^2=496.0, match=True
    a1=34, a2= 6: I(w)=(-5)+(28)w, N=949, |I(w)|^2=949.0, match=True
    a1=30, a2= 4: I(w)=(-3)+(26)w, N=763, |I(w)|^2=763.0, match=True
    a1=28, a2= 6: I(w)=(-5)+(22)w, N=619, |I(w)|^2=619.0, match=True
    a1=30, a2= 3: I(w)=(-2)+(27)w, N=787, |I(w)|^2=787.0, match=True

  N(I(w)) mod 3:
    {0: 78, 1: 222}

  I(w) mod (1-w) vs I(1) mod 3:
    Always equal: True

  Resultant Res(I(x), x^3-1) = I(1)*I(w)*I(w^2) = I(1)*N(I(w)):
