======================================================================
PART 7: The reduced formula H = 3 - 2*b0 + 6*b2
======================================================================

  From beta basis + constraint b0+b1+b2=1:
  H = b0 + 3*b1 + 9*b2 = b0 + 3*(1-b0-b2) + 9*b2 = 3 - 2*b0 + 6*b2

  H mod 6 depends ONLY on b0 mod 3:
    b0 = 0 mod 3 => H = 3 mod 6
    b0 = 1 mod 3 => H = 1 mod 6
    b0 = 2 mod 3 => H = 5 mod 6

  Verification:
    b0= -29, b2= 6: H=3-2*-29+6*6=97=97, b0%3=1, H%6=1
    b0= -32, b2= 4: H=3-2*-32+6*4=91=91, b0%3=1, H%6=1
    b0= -38, b2= 6: H=3-2*-38+6*6=115=115, b0%3=1, H%6=1
    b0= -23, b2= 4: H=3-2*-23+6*4=73=73, b0%3=1, H%6=1
    b0= -27, b2= 4: H=3-2*-27+6*4=81=81, b0%3=0, H%6=3
    b0= -19, b2= 5: H=3-2*-19+6*5=71=71, b0%3=2, H%6=5
    b0= -27, b2= 6: H=3-2*-27+6*6=93=93, b0%3=0, H%6=3
    b0= -25, b2= 4: H=3-2*-25+6*4=77=77, b0%3=2, H%6=5
    b0= -21, b2= 6: H=3-2*-21+6*6=81=81, b0%3=0, H%6=3
    b0= -26, b2= 3: H=3-2*-26+6*3=73=73, b0%3=1, H%6=1

